snippet: As they left the building that they had occupied for more than two months, the protesters said they would seize it again if the authorities did not drop all charges against political activists.
abstract: Ukranian protestors finalize amnesty deal with authorities, ending occupation of Kiev's City Hall that began in December 2013 in exchange for closing of all criminal cases related to protest movement; protestors say they will seize building again if authorities fail to drop all charges against political activists.
lead_paragraph: As they left the building that they had occupied for more than two months, the protesters said they would seize it again if the authorities did not drop all charges against political activists.

headline.main: Protesters Vacate Kiev’s City Hall in Deal for Amnesty
headline.print_headline: Protesters Vacate Kiev’s City Hall in Deal for Amnesty
